// =====================================================================
// Claude Code CLI — `~/.claude/settings.json`
// =====================================================================
// Critical: `"theme": "dark"` uses hardcoded RGB colors (24-bit ANSI
// true color) for bold, inline code, headings, etc. Those bypass the
// terminal emulator's ANSI palette entirely — so all the work in
// Antigravity/VS Code's `terminal.ansi*` settings has zero effect on
// Claude's CLI output.
//
// `"theme": "dark-ansi"` is the same dark scheme but emits standard
// 16-color ANSI codes. Now Claude's bold/code/etc. inherits whatever
// you configured `terminal.ansiBrightWhite`, `terminal.ansiCyan`,
// `terminal.ansiMagenta` to — i.e. your dimmed palette.
//
// Restart Claude Code (exit and re-launch) for the change to apply.
// =====================================================================
{
  "theme": "dark-ansi"
}
